# 🚇 TransitFlow – Smart Transport Optimization System

👉 **See [MY_CONTRIBUTION.md](./MY_CONTRIBUTION.md) for my role in this project**

---

## 🌟 Key Highlights

* 🚀 Multi-modal transport system (train, metro, bus, walking)
* ⚡ Real-time tracking using WebSocket architecture
* 📊 Route optimization based on cost, time, and efficiency
* 📈 Analytics dashboard for transport insights

---

## 🎯 Overview

TransitFlow is a smart urban transport platform that solves fragmented commuting by combining all transport systems into one seamless journey.

👉 **Think of it as:**
Google Maps Transit + Real-time tracking + Analytics system

---

## 🚨 Problem

* ❌ Fragmented transport planning across multiple apps
* ❌ No real-time updates or disruption alerts
* ❌ Inefficient route decisions
* ❌ Lack of data for transport optimization

---

## 💡 Solution

* ✅ Unified multi-modal journey planning
* ✅ Real-time tracking and disruption alerts
* ✅ Smart route optimization (fastest/cheapest)
* ✅ Data-driven insights for planning

---

## ✨ Core Features

### 🗺️ Smart Journey Planning

* Multiple route options across all transport modes
* Cost, time, and transfer breakdown
* Reliability-based route suggestions

---

### ⚡ Real-Time Tracking

* Live vehicle position updates
* Crowd level estimation
* Delay and platform alerts

---

### 🔄 Disruption Handling

* Instant delay alerts
* Automatic alternative route suggestions
* One-click route switching

---

### 📊 Analytics Dashboard

* System health monitoring
* Popular route insights
* Congestion analysis

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

* **Frontend:** React
* **Backend:** Node.js, Express
* **Real-time:** WebSocket (Socket.io)
* **Database:** MongoDB (planned)
* **Language:** JavaScript

---

## 🚀 Quick Start

```bash
# Backend
cd backend
npm install
npm start

# Frontend (new terminal)
cd frontend
npm install
npm start
```

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
backend/ → API + logic  
frontend/ → UI (React)  
docs/ → Documentation  
```

